06/03/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A two-day congress of the ruling VMRO-DPMNE opened on Saturday (March 5th) in Bitola.
Party leader and Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski kicked it off by predicting that if parliamentary elections were held tomorrow, VMRO-DPMNE would win again.
He also urged Branko Crvenkovski, leader of the main opposition party SDSM, to agree to hold snap elections without delay.
Gruevski also said that the government has managed to improve the economic climate, to implement judicial reforms and he vowed to continue to fight corruption.
More than 600 delegates are expected to re-elect Gruevski as their leader for a third time.
He is running unopposed.
(MIA, Makfax, Sitel, Kanal 5 - 05/03/11)
